def: A kind of sleeping car; also, a palace car; -- often shortenedto Pullman.
Any one of numerous species of soft-bodied Anthozoa, belongingto the order Actrinaria; an actinian.
A person licensed as a pilot. [Slang]
To reclaim; to demand the restoration of. [R.] Vattel (Trans.).
The act of gratulating or felicitating; congratulation.I shall turn my wishes into gratulations. South.
The opening through the bulwarks of a vessel by which personsenter or leave it.
One who gathers eggs; an eggler.
Departure from the ordinary type; irregularity; monstrosity."An abnormity . . . like a calf born with two heads." Mrs. Whitney.
Having the form of a crown or coronet; resembling a crown.

One who theoretically rejects every form of religious faith,and every kind of religious worship, and accepts only the facts andinfluences which are derived from the present life; also, one whobelieves that education and other matters of civil policy should bemanaged without the introduction of a religious element.
